@facturion/invoice
==================

This package is licensed under the MIT License (see LICENSE).

The JSON Schema in `data/invoice-schema.json` is the original work of this
package: a simplified JSON input format that covers the full EN 16931 semantic
model. It references the following public standards.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
EN 16931 (European e-invoicing semantic data model)
  Used for: the business terms (BT/BG) the simplified format maps onto, and the
            field-level semantics documented in the schema.
  Reference: EN 16931-1 — the standard text itself is published by CEN and the
            national standards bodies (e.g. DIN EN 16931-1).

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
UN/CEFACT and ISO code lists
  Used for: the code values referenced by the schema's enums and patterns
            (UNTDID 1001 invoice types, UNTDID 5305 VAT categories, UN/ECE
            Rec 20/21 units, ISO 3166 countries, ISO 4217 currencies).
  Friendly labels and curated subsets for these live in @facturion/codelists.
  Reference: https://unece.org/trade/uncefact/
